PAN AMERICAN PETROLEUM CORPORATION v. FEDERAL POWER COMMISSION. Nos. 6975-6977. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. Oct. 5, 1962. J. P. Hammond, Tulsa, Okl., William J. Grove and Carroll L. Gilliam, Washington, D. C., and Peter H. Holme, Jr., Ted P. Stockmar and Lucius E. Woods, Denver, Colo., for petitioner. Richard A. Solomon, Gen. Counsel, and Howard E. Wahrenbrock, Solicitor, Federal Power Commission, Washington, D. C., for respondent.

Before PICKETT, LEWIS and HILL, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Petitions to review dismissed October 5, 1962, on motion of petitioner to withdraw and dismiss the petitions to review.
